Binary Search kya hota hai?
Binary Search ek searching algorithm hai jo sorted list me kaam karta hai.
Ye "divide and conquer" approach use karta hai â€” yani har step me list ko aadha karta hai.

ğŸ”¥ Binary Search ka step-by-step tareeqa:
Middle element nikalte hain list ka.

Compare karte hain middle element ko target se:

Agar barabar hai â†’ target mil gaya! âœ…

Agar target chhota hai â†’ list ke left side me search karo.

Agar target bada hai â†’ list ke right side me search karo.

Repeat karte jao jab tak target mil na jaaye, ya list khatam na ho jaaye.

ğŸ“Š Example ke sath samjho:
Maan lo list hai:

ini
Copy
Edit
arr = [2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14]
target = 10
Steps:
List ka middle element:
mid = (0+6)//2 = 3
arr[3] = 8

Compare: 8 vs 10 â†’ 10 bada hai â†’ right side me search karte hain.

Nayi list range: index 4 to 6

Phir se middle:
mid = (4+6)//2 = 5 arr[5] = 12

Compare: 12 vs 10 â†’ 10 chhota hai â†’ left side me search karte hain.

Nayi list range: index 4 to 4

Phir se middle:
mid = (4+4)//2 = 4 arr[4] = 10

Mil gaya! Index 4 par target hai.

ğŸ“ˆ Binary Search kyu fast hai?
Har step pe list aadhi hoti hai.

Agar list me n elements hain, to sirf logâ‚‚(n) steps lagte hain.

Example: 1,000,000 elements â†’ sirf 20 steps me answer milta hai!

ğŸ’¥ Naive search me humein poori list dekhni padti hai, worst case me n steps lagte hain.

âœï¸ Binary Search ke kuch zaroori points:
Point	Detail
Sorted list zaroori hai	Agar list sorted nahi, to binary search kaam nahi karega
Time Complexity	O(log n)
Space Complexity (recursive version)	O(log n) recursion stack ke liye
ğŸ“‹ Summary ek line me:
"Binary search list ko bar bar aadha karta hai jab tak target mil nahi jaata."

